* Mm *

25:43.710 --> 25:46.178
* See, I *

25:46.212 --> 25:49.115
* Done hid for years, y'all *

25:49.148 --> 25:51.618
* Yeah *

25:51.651 --> 25:55.354
* But I'm so done hiding *

25:55.387 --> 25:58.090
* Now *

25:58.124 --> 26:01.427
* And if I were you *

26:01.460 --> 26:05.464
* I would find the time
to find myself *

26:07.634 --> 26:11.137
* 'Cause you don't know
what life will do *

26:11.170 --> 26:14.440
* What life will do *

26:14.473 --> 26:18.611
* Oh, but this is still
a simple song *

26:18.645 --> 26:22.281
* Of how hard
this life could be *

26:22.314 --> 26:24.951
* When you have nothing *

26:24.984 --> 26:26.953
* That you're living for *

26:26.986 --> 26:30.356
* Living for *

26:31.824 --> 26:33.492
* You can sing... *
(music stops)

26:33.525 --> 26:35.561
What you doing, Jamal?

26:35.594 --> 26:36.996
LUCIOUS: Your mother
almost had a heart attack

26:37.029 --> 26:38.464
looking for you.

26:38.497 --> 26:40.166
What y'all think?
I'm recording a song.

26:40.199 --> 26:42.635
Look, I'm-a have Webb
run through this whole place.

26:42.669 --> 26:44.503
We find one speck of drugs...

26:44.536 --> 26:45.805
COOKIE: That's right.
Oh, my God.

26:45.838 --> 26:46.973
Dad, I said

26:47.006 --> 26:49.075
that I am sober and clean,
and I am.

26:49.108 --> 26:50.309
Then why did you
leave rehab?

26:50.342 --> 26:51.410
Listen, what needs
to happen right now

26:51.443 --> 26:52.679
is we need to
finish this song,

26:52.712 --> 26:53.680
so y'all need to just...
(whistles)

26:53.713 --> 26:55.815
What you need to do is shut up.

26:55.848 --> 26:57.416
JAMAL:
Oh, Lord...
Bitch!

26:57.449 --> 26:59.018
You know what-- Ma, Ma!
What you need

26:59.051 --> 27:00.319
is your ass beat!
Mom, please.

27:00.352 --> 27:01.654
You don't want none of this.
Please, please. No.

27:01.688 --> 27:03.022
Yeah.
She don't.
She really don't.

27:03.055 --> 27:05.491
Why do have to go to DEFCON...
Please, stop. Ma, Dad!

27:05.524 --> 27:07.359
Mom, stop.

27:08.961 --> 27:10.529
Where I'm supposed to be

27:10.562 --> 27:12.765
and doing what I'm supposed
to be doing is right here.

27:12.799 --> 27:14.500
This is my rehab.

27:14.533 --> 27:16.068
Come on.

27:18.304 --> 27:20.039
Okay, finish your song.

27:20.072 --> 27:22.675
Thank you, Dad.

27:22.709 --> 27:25.177
I'm sorry. Come on.

27:25.211 --> 27:27.880
You can trust me, Ma. Come on.

27:27.914 --> 27:30.850
LUCIOUS:
Come on, Cook.

27:30.883 --> 27:33.986
I'll be out here to take you
home when you're done.

27:37.556 --> 27:39.158
LUCIOUS:
Sorry, y'all.

27:47.233 --> 27:49.235
*

27:53.572 --> 27:55.074
Order up.
(bell dings)

27:57.409 --> 27:59.045
* Cruisin'... *

27:59.078 --> 28:00.246
Mama?

28:02.114 --> 28:03.750
Mama!

28:06.285 --> 28:08.520
Hey, Bam,
don't leave just yet.

28:10.589 --> 28:13.225
* Baby, let's cruise... *

28:13.259 --> 28:15.928
L, man, let me explain.

28:15.962 --> 28:17.229
No, you don't speak.

28:17.263 --> 28:18.931
I speak.

28:20.432 --> 28:23.669
* Don't be confused *

28:23.702 --> 28:26.238
* The way *

28:26.272 --> 28:31.243
* Is clear *

28:31.277 --> 28:35.614
* And if you want it,
you got it forever... *

28:35.647 --> 28:39.351
You see, I understand
how things happen, Bam.

28:39.385 --> 28:42.588
Me and the Feds both know that
every man has his weakness.

28:42.621 --> 28:46.258
And in your case,
it's that sweet,

28:46.292 --> 28:49.762
loving woman out
there that raised you

28:49.796 --> 28:53.465
and then raised your little
girl when you got locked up.

28:53.499 --> 28:57.136
But when you and I
were locked up,

28:57.169 --> 29:00.807
I made a promise
to take care of them.

29:00.840 --> 29:03.776
And I did everything I could
to help your little girl,

29:03.810 --> 29:05.978
but now that she's gone...

29:08.480 --> 29:11.317
...I still kept my word
and took care your mama.

29:11.350 --> 29:13.886
The same way you're gonna
remember your P's and Q's

29:13.920 --> 29:16.488
when you get in front
of that grand jury.

29:19.325 --> 29:21.160
All right.
Here you go.

29:27.666 --> 29:30.636
We got Bam-Bam's mother home
safe and sound.

29:30.669 --> 29:33.973
Granny Gru has gone
night-night, thank God.

29:34.006 --> 29:37.176
And I just dropped off
the care package at WZVX.

29:37.209 --> 29:39.846
Check, check and check.

29:39.879 --> 29:42.181
What, am I
forgetting something?

29:42.214 --> 29:43.315
You forgetting me.

29:43.349 --> 29:44.516
Are you ser...

29:44.550 --> 29:47.019
You got me driving
all over Jersey

29:47.053 --> 29:48.187
on these dumbass errands.

29:48.220 --> 29:50.322
When are we gonna talk
about my problems though?

29:50.356 --> 29:52.424
All right, you know what?
Explain it to me, Hot Pocket.

29:52.458 --> 29:54.526
Why are you still stressing out
over that cornball Xavier?

29:54.560 --> 29:56.162
Yo, you don't get it.

29:56.195 --> 29:59.498
Ever since he got to Empire,
he's been all up in my face

29:59.531 --> 30:01.167
and doing shady stuff,
talking about,

30:01.200 --> 30:04.170
(mocking): "Oh, oh, it's just
business, it's just business."

30:04.203 --> 30:05.771
But acting like
it's personal with me.

30:05.804 --> 30:07.106
There you go. Lesson one.

30:07.139 --> 30:09.108
It's business, of course.

30:09.141 --> 30:12.344
But no matter what anybody
tells you, it's always personal.

30:12.378 --> 30:14.213
Okay, so what I do?

30:14.246 --> 30:17.549
You know what,
what more can you do?

30:17.583 --> 30:19.618
Yo.
(chuckles)

30:19.651 --> 30:21.387
All right, relax, mama.

30:21.420 --> 30:23.355
That's not for you.

30:23.389 --> 30:25.557
Just let the universe
work its magic.

30:25.591 --> 30:27.026
Okay?

30:27.059 --> 30:28.227
It's got you.

30:28.260 --> 30:30.229
Type of Shaolin monk bull...

30:30.262 --> 30:33.132
You know what?
You have wasted my entire day.

30:33.165 --> 30:34.800
(Thirsty humming koto music)

30:34.833 --> 30:36.035
BECKY:
Waste of time.

30:36.068 --> 30:37.736
THIRSTY:
Shaolin Wu-Tang.

30:40.672 --> 30:42.041
ROSS:
So Lucious Lyon wins again.

30:42.074 --> 30:44.043
You built this case up
on one star witness,

30:44.076 --> 30:46.378
Bam-Bam King, who suddenly
refuses to testify.

30:46.412 --> 30:47.713
Yeah, Lyon must've
got to him somehow.

30:47.746 --> 30:49.581
He murdered Frank Gathers,
and I can prove it.

30:49.615 --> 30:50.883
I just need more time.

30:50.917 --> 30:52.384
Agent, your time is up;
as of right now,

30:52.418 --> 30:53.986
you're off the case,
'cause it's closed.

30:54.020 --> 30:55.988
What?
But I have more leads, sir.

30:56.022 --> 30:58.057
Any evidence
against the target is tainted

30:58.090 --> 30:59.725
due to your omission of the fact

30:59.758 --> 31:02.061
that he is your
half-brother.

31:02.094 --> 31:04.463
I'm putting you on paid leave.

31:13.272 --> 31:15.107
REPORTER: Mr. Dubois' campaign
got a much needed

31:15.141 --> 31:16.608
breath of life when Jayce Jones

31:16.642 --> 31:18.677
came forward to confirm that
he served time

31:18.710 --> 31:20.913
for the manslaughter death
of Carla Mills,

31:20.947 --> 31:23.515
who drowned in a lake
over 20 years ago.

31:23.549 --> 31:25.251
And most important,
that Angelo Dubois

31:25.284 --> 31:27.253
was nowhere near the scene
when it happened.

31:27.286 --> 31:29.021
(mutes TV)

31:29.055 --> 31:30.422
God.

31:30.456 --> 31:32.191
Dad went so low.

31:32.224 --> 31:34.526
Are you surprised?

31:34.560 --> 31:36.495
Always and never.

31:37.729 --> 31:39.765
What?

31:39.798 --> 31:41.500
(sighs)

31:42.801 --> 31:46.105
I'm gonna keep this short...

31:46.138 --> 31:47.473
and real.

31:49.308 --> 31:50.977
Are you a dope fiend?

31:56.748 --> 31:57.916
(sighs)

31:59.651 --> 32:02.288
Look, I got caught up, Ma.

32:02.321 --> 32:04.991
I ain't even trying
to run away from that.

32:05.024 --> 32:07.893
But I swear on my music
and everything else

32:07.926 --> 32:09.996
that I've been fighting back for
since I came back

32:10.029 --> 32:13.565
from the bullet, I...
I'm done with the pills.

32:13.599 --> 32:15.467
Really.

32:15.501 --> 32:16.969
I'm so focused.

32:17.003 --> 32:18.804
I'm not even trying to have
any kind of substance

32:18.837 --> 32:19.838
mess with that.

32:22.841 --> 32:24.977
I'm happy to hear that, baby.

32:25.011 --> 32:26.145
(chuckles)

32:26.178 --> 32:29.481
(sighs)

32:29.515 --> 32:32.351
Finally feels like
everything's gonna be all right.

32:32.384 --> 32:34.520
You're okay.

32:34.553 --> 32:37.423
Angelo's situation
is settled.

32:37.456 --> 32:39.358
He's back on
his campaign, so...

32:39.391 --> 32:41.260
Yeah, he's good, right?

32:41.293 --> 32:42.528
We'll see.

32:42.561 --> 32:45.031
I mean, it's politics;
all they got to do is say it,

32:45.064 --> 32:47.366
it sticks to you like stink.

32:49.401 --> 32:52.304
Lucious did all of
that just for you.

32:55.541 --> 32:57.843
That is a twisted
kind of love, man.

32:57.876 --> 32:59.911
I know he's planning
his next move.

33:09.088 --> 33:11.490
*

33:20.099 --> 33:22.634
LUCIOUS:
Now, before we get started,

33:22.668 --> 33:25.404
let's take care
of a short order of business.

33:25.437 --> 33:26.805
Xavier.

33:26.838 --> 33:28.540
You're fired.

33:28.574 --> 33:30.642
GUARD:
All right, let's go.

33:30.676 --> 33:32.411
Whoa, come on, man!
What the hell?

33:32.444 --> 33:35.047
Let this serve as an example
for each and every one of you.

33:35.081 --> 33:37.149
If I catch anybody
getting kickbacks,

33:37.183 --> 33:39.718
trust me, the next time
you'll get much more

33:39.751 --> 33:41.220
than fired.

33:41.253 --> 33:42.421
XAVIER:
Mr. Lyon, Mr. Lyon,

33:42.454 --> 33:43.555
I would never
do that to you, man.

33:43.589 --> 33:44.590
I swear to God,
I'm innocent on this!

33:44.623 --> 33:45.591
Innocent?

33:45.624 --> 33:46.992
Tell that
to the program director

33:47.025 --> 33:48.927
over at WZVX.

33:48.960 --> 33:49.995
You run a sloppy
business, man, sloppy.

33:50.028 --> 33:52.064
Come on, now,
that's a lie! Becky!

33:52.098 --> 33:53.899
Becky, you know me.
All right? You know me.

33:53.932 --> 33:55.667
You need to vouch for me.
Come on.

33:55.701 --> 33:58.670
I don't know you, man.
It's just business.

33:58.704 --> 33:59.738
"Just business"?

33:59.771 --> 34:00.772
Bye.

34:00.806 --> 34:02.741
Yo, I'm innocent, man!

34:02.774 --> 34:04.243
Yo, I didn't do this!

34:04.276 --> 34:06.912
Get off me!

34:06.945 --> 34:08.180
Go on out of here.

34:08.214 --> 34:09.781
Now that the fireworks are over,

34:09.815 --> 34:11.750
I'm sure you've all
heard my announcement

34:11.783 --> 34:16.255
about Inferno, even though it
may have been muffled a bit by

34:16.288 --> 34:17.756
certain people
in this room.
Uh, Lucious, look,

34:17.789 --> 34:19.091
everyone in this room

34:19.125 --> 34:20.759
is very busy,
so if you could go ahead,

34:20.792 --> 34:22.928
and finish what
you have to say, thank you.

34:22.961 --> 34:24.130
I'm getting there.

34:27.133 --> 34:30.436
We are Lyons;
therefore, we roar.

34:30.469 --> 34:32.971
So from this point forward,
each and every employee

34:33.004 --> 34:35.441
of this company,
their number one priority

34:35.474 --> 34:37.109
is to make sure that

34:37.143 --> 34:39.445
Inferno is what it should be.

34:39.478 --> 34:41.147
It's an album

34:41.180 --> 34:42.614
I'm producing.

34:42.648 --> 34:45.617
I'm going to have the
top artists from Empire on it,

34:45.651 --> 34:47.486
and I'm hoping
that my son, Jamal,

34:47.519 --> 34:50.322
will bless me
with a song.

34:50.356 --> 34:52.624
Now, seeing that the position
of head of A&R

34:52.658 --> 34:53.792
has recently just opened,

34:53.825 --> 34:56.728
I decided to fill it
with someone that I feel is

34:56.762 --> 34:59.965
worthy of such a position.

34:59.998 --> 35:03.169
And as a result of being
in this position,

35:03.202 --> 35:06.638
she's come to be under
a great deal of anguish and fire

35:06.672 --> 35:07.973
from me because she's been

35:08.006 --> 35:11.076
my biggest critic,
which in turn turned her

35:11.109 --> 35:15.314
into my greatest ally,
and she's very loyal.

35:15.347 --> 35:19.151
And I was so hesitant
to appoint her in this position

35:19.185 --> 35:20.819
because I didn't want
to take her away

35:20.852 --> 35:22.588
from her first
responsibility,

35:22.621 --> 35:25.991
and that's the job
of being a mother.

35:26.024 --> 35:29.328
But she will serve me
as she has for years,

35:29.361 --> 35:32.097
as my muse who has lit

35:32.130 --> 35:34.333
an inferno inside of me.

35:34.366 --> 35:36.502
She is the DNA
of this company,

35:36.535 --> 35:40.706
my wife, Mrs. Anika Lyon.

35:40.739 --> 35:42.140
(chuckles)

35:44.743 --> 35:46.111
Your new head of A&R.

35:46.144 --> 35:47.145
Thank you.

35:48.714 --> 35:50.716
Thank you.

35:57.055 --> 35:58.424
Congrats.

36:04.062 --> 36:06.232
Come on.
Take your seat.

36:06.265 --> 36:07.999
Ha! Nice and warm for you.

36:21.747 --> 36:23.449
("Inferno" playing)

36:26.585 --> 36:29.255
("Inferno" continues
over speakers)

36:31.690 --> 36:34.025
(door opens, slams)

36:36.628 --> 36:41.733
Mm, mm-mm, that
is fire, Lucious.

36:41.767 --> 36:43.835
Yeah, "Inferno." (chuckles)

36:43.869 --> 36:45.404
The name fits.

36:45.437 --> 36:47.606
What, you want
some trouble, Cookie?

36:47.639 --> 36:51.943
No, no, I-I don't want
no trouble, Lucious.

36:51.977 --> 36:54.713
I just have
some questions, is all.

36:57.383 --> 36:59.618
Like, this-this
album right here.

36:59.651 --> 37:03.589
This was your first
album to go gold.

37:03.622 --> 37:06.858
Now, I remember working
on that six months

37:06.892 --> 37:10.028
before I went to prison.

37:10.061 --> 37:13.632
So, whose DNA is in that,
Lucious? Huh?

37:16.735 --> 37:18.637
(laughs)

37:18.670 --> 37:20.806
DNA. Boy, please.

37:23.675 --> 37:26.312
Ain't nothing but a hood rat.

37:26.345 --> 37:28.347
(glass shatters)

37:31.149 --> 37:33.652
(glass shatters)

37:33.685 --> 37:36.455
All right.

37:36.488 --> 37:37.989
Let's play.

37:44.863 --> 37:46.298
Did I tell you,

37:46.332 --> 37:48.467
I watched you on TV

37:48.500 --> 37:50.802
in that dirty-ass rec room

37:50.836 --> 37:56.074
in Danbury when Empire's
first album was inducted

37:56.107 --> 37:58.644
into the Music Hall of Fame.

37:58.677 --> 38:01.146
(glass shatters)

38:01.179 --> 38:03.014
(chuckles)

38:03.048 --> 38:04.683
Who was your muse for that?

38:04.716 --> 38:05.851
You done, bitch?

38:05.884 --> 38:06.985
Huh, Lucious?

38:07.018 --> 38:08.153
Don't you come any closer.

38:08.186 --> 38:10.322
Put it down.
(grunts)

38:10.356 --> 38:13.024
Who was your muse
on that, huh?!

38:13.058 --> 38:15.327
Who was your muse, Lucious?

38:15.361 --> 38:18.029
Oh, do you remember this one?

38:18.063 --> 38:19.331
Because I do.

38:19.365 --> 38:21.600
Yeah, I sent tapes
from the inside

38:21.633 --> 38:25.203
back and forth with you while
you worked on them out here.

38:26.204 --> 38:28.206
(laughs)

38:28.239 --> 38:30.676
Oh! And this one.

38:30.709 --> 38:33.211
This is when you stopped
coming to visit me.

38:33.244 --> 38:35.013
It was weak.

38:35.046 --> 38:36.715
All the critics said so.

38:40.386 --> 38:42.220
Yeah, get up.

38:42.253 --> 38:44.890
None of this would've
existed without me!

38:44.923 --> 38:46.625
Not those gold records!

38:46.658 --> 38:48.193
Not those plaques!

38:48.226 --> 38:50.028
Not this studio!

38:50.061 --> 38:51.963
None of it!

38:51.997 --> 38:54.232
So you tell me, Lucious.

38:54.265 --> 38:57.369
Tell me whose DNA is running
all through it, huh?

38:57.403 --> 39:01.239
Who's the mother with
the important job, Lucious?!

39:01.272 --> 39:02.240
You tell me.

39:02.273 --> 39:03.409
I gave you three sons,

39:03.442 --> 39:06.044
bitch, three sons!

39:06.077 --> 39:07.746
I had a miscarriage.

39:08.914 --> 39:11.917
I went to jail for 17 years

39:11.950 --> 39:13.251
so you could build this!

39:14.920 --> 39:15.987
So you could build this Empire!

39:16.021 --> 39:17.456
(shouts)

39:18.924 --> 39:19.925
(shouts)

39:19.958 --> 39:21.226
COOKIE:
Yeah, follow me!

39:21.259 --> 39:23.495
I'll show you whose DNA
is in here.

39:23.529 --> 39:25.431
Okay, now you die!

39:25.464 --> 39:28.734
You said Lyons roar?
Well, let me hear you roar.

39:28.767 --> 39:29.901
Yeah, I came here

39:29.935 --> 39:31.537
to make a lot of noise.

39:32.638 --> 39:35.273
Now you die!

39:36.442 --> 39:37.809
Go home.

39:41.447 --> 39:43.482
COOKIE:
I'm just getting started.
(elevator bell dings)

39:56.962 --> 40:00.466
(piano keys pounding)

40:05.303 --> 40:07.739
(grunting)

40:27.993 --> 40:31.129
Trying to erase me, Lucious?

40:31.162 --> 40:32.698
Huh?

40:36.868 --> 40:38.837
After all
I done for you.

40:38.870 --> 40:43.141
(crying):
I did 17 years for this family.

40:43.174 --> 40:45.343
You built this company
on my back.

40:47.713 --> 40:50.081
(crying)

40:50.115 --> 40:52.484
And you just gonna give it
to that bitch.

40:52.518 --> 40:54.185
Is that your plan, Lucious?

40:54.219 --> 40:56.855
Huh?!

40:56.888 --> 40:58.524
(shouts)

40:58.557 --> 40:59.758
Let go of me!

40:59.791 --> 41:01.693
Stop.
(grunting)

41:05.697 --> 41:07.699
(panting)

41:34.259 --> 41:36.261
(teapot whistling)

41:41.399 --> 41:43.902
(whistling stops)

41:53.912 --> 41:56.181
(playing "Simple Song")

42:13.799 --> 42:16.602
*

42:22.473 --> 42:24.943
(moaning)

42:43.829 --> 42:45.764
Mm-mm.

42:45.797 --> 42:47.599
No.

42:47.633 --> 42:51.269
I said I was done with you.

42:51.302 --> 42:53.338
I meant that.

42:57.342 --> 42:59.344
*

44:00.371 --> 44:01.372
Yeah.

44:01.406 --> 44:03.374
Captioned by
Media Access Group at WGBH

44:05.310 --> 44:06.978
ANNOUNCER: You've just
watched Empire.

44:07.012 --> 44:09.748
Now here are a few more shows
to check out from Fox.

44:11.482 --> 44:13.218
(gunshot)

44:13.251 --> 44:15.520
Shots Fired is
a murder mystery.

44:15.553 --> 44:18.356
An African-American officer
kills an unarmed white guy.

44:18.389 --> 44:21.126
I asked him
to step out of the vehicle,
but as he steps out,

44:21.159 --> 44:23.361
he reaches for my gun,
and it was either him or me.

